title: highestprofile
extract: high-profile adjective [ before noun ] uk ​ /ˌhaɪˈprəʊ.faɪl/ us ​ /ˌhaɪˈproʊ.faɪl/ C2 attracting a lot of attention and interest from the public and newspapers, television, etc.: high-profile politicians. He resigned from a high-profile job as economic adviser to the president.
